  "prompt": "What is the best gaming PC I can get for 1400\u20ac?",
  "response": "Building or buying a gaming PC for \u20ac1400 can yield an excellent system that can handle most modern games at high settings. Here\u2019s a guideline on components you should consider for a gaming PC within that budget:\n\n### Option A: Pre-built Gaming PC\nIf you prefer a pre-built system, look for these specifications:\n1. **CPU:** AMD Ryzen 5 5600X or Intel Core i5-12400F\n2. **GPU:** NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060/3060 Ti or AMD Radeon RX 6700 XT\n3. **RAM:** 16GB DDR4 (3200 MHz or higher)\n4. **Storage:** 1TB NVMe SSD (this provides speed for loading games)\n5. **Motherboard:** Compatible B550 or Z490 motherboard\n6. **Power Supply:** 650W 80+ Bronze\n7. **Case:** Mid-tower case with good airflow\n8. **Cooling:** Stock cooler (decent for Ryzen) or aftermarket cooler for Intel\n\n### Option B: Custom Build\nIf you're comfortable building your own PC, here\u2019s a suggested build:\n\n1. **CPU:** AMD Ryzen 5 5600X - \u20ac220\n2. **GPU:** NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3060 Ti - \u20ac400\n3. **RAM:** Corsair Vengeance LPX 16GB (2x8GB) DDR4 3200MHz - \u20ac80\n4. **Storage:** Crucial P3 1TB NVMe SSD - \u20ac100\n5. **Motherboard:** MSI B550-A PRO - \u20ac110\n6. **Power Supply:** Corsair CV650, 650W 80+ Bronze - \u20ac70\n7. **Case:** NZXT H510 - \u20ac70\n8. **Cooling:** Cooler Master Hyper 212 (optional) - \u20ac35\n\n### Total: Approx. \u20ac1,175\n\nThis leaves you some budget for peripherals (monitor, keyboard, mouse) or upgrades (like higher RAM or additional storage) depending on your needs.\n\n### Important Considerations:\n- **GPU Prices:** Prices can fluctuate due to market conditions. If a specific GPU is out of stock or overpriced, check for alternatives like the AMD RX 6600 or RTX 3050.\n- **Futureproofing:** Ensure that your components can be upgraded in the future. Motherboards with additional RAM slots and PCIe slots are useful.\n- **Local Availability:** Check local retailers or online stores in your region (like Amazon.de, Mindfactory, or Alternate) for stock and prices.\n- **Building vs. Buying:** If building seems daunting, pre-built systems are a great option but may have a markup.\n\n### Conclusion\nWith a budget of \u20ac1400, you can configure a powerful gaming PC capable of handling modern titles for years to come, especially by balancing CPU and GPU capabilities. Always check the latest components and prices as they can vary significantly over time.",
